                        GEORGE CLARK
                   (policeman, E 145). I produce a certificate—(Read: ("Clerkenwell Sessions; 


                        James Brown, Convicted, Dec., 1851, of breaking and entering a shop, and stealing a quantity of boots and shoes; 
Confined twelve months")—I was present at the trial—the prisoner is the person.





                        WILLIAM LOCKEY
                  . I produce a certificate—(Head: Guildhall Sessions, April, 1855; 



                        Mary Ann Jones, cortvicted of stealing a handkerchief from the person; 
Confined six months.) I was present, Clark is the woman.
